# 🔥 Basic DOM Interview Questions

## 1. What is DOM?

### ✅ Answer:

**English:**
DOM (Document Object Model) is a tree-like structure representing HTML elements as objects, allowing JavaScript to manipulate them.

**Hindi:**
DOM एक tree structure है जो HTML elements को objects में बदल देता है ताकि JavaScript उन्हें बदल सके।

---

## 2. Difference between HTML and DOM?

| HTML                 | DOM                    |
| -------------------- | ---------------------- |
| Static               | Dynamic                |
| Written code         | Browser representation |
| Cannot change itself | Can be changed via JS  |

👉 हिंदी:
HTML = static code
DOM = live structure (जिसे JS बदल सकता है)

---

## 3. What is a Node in DOM?

👉 Every element, attribute, or text is a **node**

**Example:**

```html
<p>Hello</p>
```

* `<p>` → element node
* "Hello" → text node

---

## 4. Difference: getElementById vs querySelector

| Feature     | getElementById | querySelector   |
| ----------- | -------------- | --------------- |
| Speed       | Faster         | Slightly slower |
| Selector    | Only ID        | CSS selectors   |
| Flexibility | Less           | More            |

👉 Hindi:
querySelector ज्यादा powerful है

---

# 🔥 Intermediate DOM Questions

## 5. Difference: innerText vs innerHTML vs textContent

| Property    | Meaning            |
| ----------- | ------------------ |
| innerText   | Visible text only  |
| textContent | All text           |
| innerHTML   | Includes HTML tags |

**Example:**

```javascript
el.innerHTML = "<b>Hello</b>";
```

👉 हिंदी:
innerHTML HTML को भी समझता है

---

## 6. What is Event Bubbling?

### ✅ Answer:

Event starts from child → goes to parent

```javascript
child → parent → document
```

👉 हिंदी:
event नीचे से ऊपर जाता है

---

## 7. What is Event Capturing?

Opposite of bubbling

```javascript
document → parent → child
```

👉 हिंदी:
event ऊपर से नीचे आता है

---

## 8. What is Event Delegation?

### ✅ Concept:

Using a parent to handle events for children

```javascript
document.querySelector("ul").addEventListener("click", function(e) {
    if(e.target.tagName === "LI") {
        console.log("Clicked", e.target);
    }
});
```

👉 हिंदी:
एक parent से multiple children handle करना

---

## 9. Difference: HTMLCollection vs NodeList

| Feature | HTMLCollection | NodeList     |
| ------- | -------------- | ------------ |
| Live    | Yes            | No (mostly)  |
| Methods | Limited        | More methods |

---

## 10. What is document object?

👉 Root object of DOM

```javascript
document.body
document.title
```

👉 हिंदी:
document = पूरे page का entry point

---

# 🔥 Advanced DOM Questions

## 11. How to create and add elements?

```javascript
let el = document.createElement("div");
el.innerText = "Hello";
document.body.appendChild(el);
```

---

## 12. Difference: append vs appendChild

| append         | appendChild |
| -------------- | ----------- |
| Multiple items | Only one    |
| Text allowed   | Only nodes  |

---

## 13. How to remove elements?

```javascript
element.remove();
```

OR

```javascript
parent.removeChild(child);
```

---

## 14. What is closest() method?

```javascript
el.closest("div");
```

👉 Finds nearest parent

👉 हिंदी:
सबसे पास वाला matching parent

---

## 15. What is classList?

```javascript
el.classList.add("active");
el.classList.remove("active");
el.classList.toggle("active");
```

👉 हिंदी:
CSS class manage करने के लिए

---

# 🔥 Scenario-Based Questions (Very Important 🔥)

## 16. Add item to list on button click

```javascript
btn.addEventListener("click", function() {
    let li = document.createElement("li");
    li.innerText = "New Item";
    list.appendChild(li);
});
```

---

## 17. Change background color on click

```javascript
document.body.addEventListener("click", function() {
    document.body.style.backgroundColor = "yellow";
});
```

---

## 18. Get input value and show it

```javascript
let value = document.getElementById("input").value;
console.log(value);
```

---

# 🔥 Tricky Interview Questions

## 19. Why is DOM manipulation slow?

👉 Because it updates UI (reflow + repaint)

👉 हिंदी:
Browser को बार-बार render करना पड़ता है

---

## 20. What is reflow and repaint?

* **Reflow:** layout change
* **Repaint:** visual change

---

## 21. What is defer in script?

```html
<script src="app.js" defer></script>
```

👉 Loads JS after HTML parsing

---

## 22. Difference: onclick vs addEventListener

| onclick     | addEventListener  |
| ----------- | ----------------- |
| One handler | Multiple handlers |
| Old method  | Modern method     |

